The evidence with the title 'Christianization Of Iberia - Wikipedia ' says The Christianization Of Iberia refers to the spread of Christianity in an early 4th century by the sermon of Saint Nino in an ancient Georgian kingdom of Kartli , known as Iberia in the Classical Antiquity , which resulted in declaring it as a state religion by then - pagan king Mirian III ... Some of the third - century burials in Georgia include Christian objects such  ... 
